               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t16930426-27-off118-c85" targOrder="Y" targets="t16930426-27-defend85 t16930426-27-off118 t16930426-27-verdict120"></join>
         
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t16930426-27-defend85" type="defendantName">
                  John 
                  Ogle
               <interp inst="t16930426-27-defend85" type="surname" value="Ogle"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16930426-27-defend85" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16930426-27-defend85" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , was Indicted for <rs id="t16930426-27-off118" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16930426-27-off118" type="offenceCategory" value="sexual"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16930426-27-off118" type="offenceSubcategory" value="bigamy"></interp>
               Felony in Marrying Two Wives, the first one 
                     <persName id="t16930426-27-victim86" type="victimName">
                        Sarah 
                        Haslam
                     <interp inst="t16930426-27-victim86" type="surname" value="Haslam"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t16930426-27-victim86" type="given" value="Sarah"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t16930426-27-victim86" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                     </persName>
                  , whom he Married at the Parish of East Ardsley in the County of York, in the Second year of the late King James; the second, one 
                     <persName id="t16930426-27-victim87" type="victimName">
                        Mary 
                        Ivey
                     <interp inst="t16930426-27-victim87" type="surname" value="Ivey"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t16930426-27-victim87" type="given" value="Mary"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t16930426-27-victim87" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                     </persName>
                  , whom he Married at <placeName id="t16930426-27-crimeloc119">Westminster</placeName>
                     <interp inst="t16930426-27-crimeloc119" type="placeName" value="Westminster"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16930426-27-crimeloc119" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                     <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t16930426-27-off118 t16930426-27-crimeloc119"></join> in January last
            </rs>. The Evidence swore that he was Married to Haslam, for one of the Witnesses gave her in Marriage, and that he Cohabited with her, and had two Children by Haslam; the Certificate was produced in Court that was written by the Minister; there were others that corroborated the Matter fully upon him, how that he owned several times that he had Married the said Haslam; the Prisoner denied the Fact, and that he only Lodged in the House of Haslam, being an Inn; but that did not serve his turn; and he owned the Marriage to Ivey in Court, but denied the first; he was found <rs id="t16930426-27-verdict120" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16930426-27-verdict120" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               guilty
            </rs> of Felony.</p>
